xmlrpc-epi
------------------------------------------
xmlrpc-epi is an implementation of the xmlrpc protocol in C. It provides 
an easy to use API for developers to serialize RPC requests to and from 
XML. It does *not* include a transport layer, such as HTTP. The API is 
primarily based upon proprietary code written for internal usage at 
Epinions.com, and was later modified to incorporate concepts from the 
xmlrpc protocol. It passed the xmlrpc validation test suite in December 
2000.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-11
  libexpat1-2.0.1-1
  libiconv2-1.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.10-1.10.1-1
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.9-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool-2.2.2-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://xmlrpc-epi.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/xmlrpc-epi/files

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack xmlrpc-epi-0.54-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./xmlrpc-epi-0.54-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxmlrpc-epi-devel-0.54-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxmlrpc-epi0-0.54-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xmlrpc-epi-0.54-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xmlrpc-epi-0.54-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

